  "text": "While the first and second datasets are utilized for nodule detection assessment, the third and fourth sets of CT lung images are specifically used for the main goal of our research that is nodule growth rate measurement. These two datasets comprise several sets of consecutive images captured from some patients in different dates. The images of the third set (hereafter, called as \"ELCAP2\") are taken from the database of the Cornel University, while the fourth set (called as RIDER) contains lung CT images taken from The Cancer Imaging Archive (TCIA) [CITATION_1] .",
